The 42-year-old Ditta passed on the information to the criminals because of fears that his cocaine addiction would be revealed.
Today at the Liverpool Royal Court Ditta, who works for the law firm Forbes Solicitors, located in Blackburn, was covered with shame after acknowledging his guilt in two cases of intentional obstruction of justice following a three-week trial at the Liverpool Crown Court.
