However, this has largely crossed the boundaries of the usual lawyer-client relationship.
He has prevented police investigations as much as possible to allow these individuals to continue their criminal activities.
Mr. Ditta did not honor his profession, but disgraced it.
He became too close to certain clients, in particular Scarborough, and allowed himself to doubt his disinterest.
Ditta pleaded not guilty and said, “If I were a corrupt lawyer who I am not, and I wanted to give information to Mr. Scarborough, I wouldn’t have waited 15 hours, I would have done it immediately.”
But after the meeting, senior officer Lee Halstead of Lancashire Police said: “Mr. Ditta turned from a criminal lawyer to a criminal as soon as he started buying drugs from organized crime.”
