FAU: “Air passengers can now use gadgets on airplanes (but do not call from a mobile phone)”
Air passengers will be able to use their electronic devices throughout the flight to read, work, play games, watch movies and listen to music, but not speak on mobile phones, according to long-awaited new guidelines released Thursday by the Federal Aviation Administration.
But passengers should not expect the changes to take place immediately.
How quickly such a change is implemented will vary depending on the airline, said FAA administrator Michael Huerta at a press conference.
