“Today, the Egyptian people have laid the foundations for a new life — absolute freedom, true democracy and stability,” said Morsi, a 60-year-old American-educated engineer from the Muslim Brotherhood, a fundamentalist group that for most of its 84 years has been a banned organization that has served as a target for the hard-hitting actions of successive governments.
